  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently we are targeting esnext in every tsoconfig file in lodestar.\r\nEsnext is not fully supported in nodejs 12 which means we could have runtime errors if we use such unsupported feature.\r\n\r\nSolution:\r\n- change target to es2018 (fully supported by node12)\r\n- replace all 12n bigint literals with BigInt(12) - following regex does that automatically `\\s+(\\d+)n` => `BigInt($1)`\r\n\r\nThis will allow us to use all node12 goodies like optional chaining and it will warn us if we try to use some unsupported esnext stuff (we enabled only esnext.bigint lib as it's supported by node12)",
