    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> Shouldn't Babel took care of the transpilation of those features?\r\n\r\nContext: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/59787574/typescript-tsconfig-settings-for-node-js-12\r\n\r\n tldr nodejs supports some bigint features available in estarget beyond es2019 but laks some other, so if we set target to esnext, \r\ntranspiled code could contain some features not supported by node12 but it's gonna fail only at runtime.\r\n\r\nBabel is fine since it transpiles to code compatible with nodejs version while tsonfig (which we use for typechecking and some other stuff) targets es versions.",
